Jenni Evans, News24(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Port Alfred -&nbsp;A black bag containing 2kg of the recreational drug methamphetamine was found under the seat of a car that had raised suspicions in Port Alfred, Eastern Cape police said.Police pulled the vehicle over at around 08:30 in Albany road in the seaside town on Saturday and made the find in a black refuse bag stashed under the driver's seat, Captain Mali Govender said. Police valued the stash at around R400 000. They also found four Mandrax tablets valued at R80. A 49-year-old man was arrested on a charge of possession and dealing in drugs and will appear in the Port Alfred Magistrate's Court on Monday. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.